    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="46" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <head>No. 44.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jones</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-07-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 7, 1874</date>. (Rec’d
                            July 20.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 273.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith copy of
                        Count d’ Aspremont Lynden’s letter in regard to the termination of the
                        treaty between the United States and Belgium of July, 1858.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. R. JONES.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Count <persName type="from">d’Aspremont
                                    Lynden</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Jones</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of Foreign Affairs</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-07-07">
                                <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 7,
                                1874</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of the letter which you were pleased to address to me, under
                            date of the 1st instant, to give me notice of the resolution <pb facs="0162" n="66" xml:id="pg_66"/> which the Government of the
                            United States has thought fit to take to annul the treaty of commerce
                            and navigation of July 17, 1858.</p>
                    <p>You are of opinion, sir, that the term of twelve months which is to
                            follow the notification will begin from the day of the reception by my
                            department of the communication of July 1.</p>
                    <p>The letter referred to reached me on the same day upon which it was
                            sent.</p>
                    <p>The government of the King concurs with you, sir, that the treaty above
                            mentioned will cease to have effect on July 1, 1875.</p>
                    <p>I take, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>COUNT D’ASPREMONT LYNDEN.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell Jones</hi>, &amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                &amp;c., <hi rend="italic">Brussels.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
